<TITLE> Cox's Bazar road accident kills 14 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, Feb 21 (bdnews24.com)  A bus packed with picnickers lost control and rammed into an electricity pole Thursday, killing at least 14 people on the Chittagong-Cox's Bazar Road, an official said. Another 20 people were injured in the accident. The bus caught fire after crashing into the electric pole as it tried to swerve past a speeding truck on the road, accident survivors said. The dead include six women and one child. The accident occurred around 11am. Rescuers recovered 14 bodies from the site of the accident and sent the injured to hospital, said Sajjadul Hasan, deputy commissioner for Cox's Bazar. bdnews2
